CDX (more accurately -BuildCDX) is 100% dependent on XCRI data in the plugin *and* the csg/psg file used for shared geometry:
1. -BuildCDX on a plugin without appropriately updated XCRI data will produce:
2. -BuildCDX on a plugin without a matching CSG or PSG file will produce:
3. -BuildCDX on a plugin without matching precombined NIFS will produce:

RENDERING:                              Failed to find static geometry id (0x83b0b913, 0x 583c712), generating dummy data.

It also appears that a given CSG or PSG file only needs to be loaded before the point of -BuildCDX. This means a master of a plugin passed to -BuildCDX which loads it's own CSG/PSG data related to the plugin being built will still succeed. This implies that the game/CK loads this CSG/PSG data into an internal memory structure which is consulted by -BuildCDX along with cell XCRI data and physical precombined NIFs. On top of that, this all works with esp plugins, atleast with CK. e.g. this works:

clayne@a4-sfx:/cygdrive/c/Program Files (x86)/Steam/steamapps/common/Fallout 4/ckgen.build/1 (modded_regrowth) $ plugin-master-reloc -v Data/3DNPC_FO4.esp.precombine_merge.all.01.esp
Data/3DNPC_FO4.esp.precombine_merge.all.01.esp:
[00] Fallout4.esm
[01] 3DNPC_FO4.esp

clayne@a4-sfx:/cygdrive/c/Program Files (x86)/Steam/steamapps/common/Fallout 4/ckgen.build/1 (modded_regrowth) $ ./CreationKit.exe -buildcdx:3DNPC_FO4.esp.precombine_merge.all.01.esp
MemoryTraceWrite::MemoryTraceWrite
Initialized small stack
Set thread processor
Set thread priority

Handles during -BuildCDX:3DNPC_FO4.esp.precombine_merge.all.01.esp:

 4AA8: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\cdxtmp
 4B10: File  (RWD)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\materials
 4B14: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\3DNPC_FO4.esp.precombine_merge.all.01.esp
 4B18: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\Fallout4.esm
 4B24: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\3DNPC_FO4.esp
 4B28: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\3DNPC_FO4 - Main.ba2
 4B2C: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\3DNPC_FO4 - Textures.ba2
 4B30: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\3DNPC_FO4 - Geometry.psg
 4B34: File  (R--)   C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout 4.modded_regrowth\ckgen.build\1\Data\3DNPC_FO4 - Geometry.csg

Even using the intermediary CombinedObjects.esp doesn't matter, as long as it has a master which loads the requisite PSG (packed shared geometry) data (or CSG if compressed). Also, it doesn't matter if a CSG or PSG file is used, CK (and the game) will try to use both. CSG is merely a size optimization for PSG files after they've been generated (most likely zlib or lz4 compressed).

Also, -BuildCDX might want to be done after everything has been generated (PC+PV) as the output differs based on the contents of the esp or esm.

