---

General difficulties:

1. xEdit doesn't allow editing Fallout4.esm. This would be useful for the intermediate step between merging XCRI data and generating new previs data.
2. CK has max handle limitations for forms/objects. This speaks for itself and means one cannot just open their entire load order in CK and generate precombines once. Really sucks and makes things a lot harder to setup for previs generation.
3. CK has max handle limitations for loose files. This means 100k+ loose precombine files will result in CK crashing and not generating complete previs data. The only way around this is to temporarily rearchive the new precombined NIFs with the vanilla archives and shim that into place before previs generation.
4. CK -generateprecombined and -generateprevisdata require atleast one REFR in each cell to be generating. Simply providing a plugin of overidden cell data won't do anything without actual statics to generate for.
5. CK likes to remove all esps from the master list of a plugin and provide broken formids for anything those esps were master for. The only fix is to manually readd them in xEdit but one cannot use "add masters" as this will increment all the broken references. Instead the main header must be edited. This sucks.
6. CK likes to trash the master id of XPRI formids if more than 2 masters are used.
7. xEdit doesn't allow more than 254 plugins so even if the plugins in the list aren't actually going to be loaded there's still an issue with generating more plugins than the maximum load order can handle.
8. xEdit has a bug where if during the process of copying an element if masters are somehow added around the same time then it can produce broken worldspace references that have the wrong load order formid. Still investigating.
